columns.description: Universal time of the sample at the spacecraft.  The time appears as 6 integer columns (year, day of year, hour, minute, seconds, millisecond). Individual elements of the time column are separated by a single ASCII space character and have leading zeros omitted.  The individual elements can be read by using the following FORTRAN format:'(2X,I4,1X,I3,3(1X,I2),1X,I3)' IYR IDOY IHR IMIN ISEC IMSEC
columns.name: SAMPLE UTC

columns.description: Decimal day of year.  This column provides a second representation of the sample time.
columns.name: DECIMAL DAY

columns.description: B-field X-component in Planetocentric coordinate system.
columns.name: BX PLANETOCENTRIC

columns.description: B-field Y-component in Planetocentric coordinate system.
columns.name: BY PLANETOCENTRIC

columns.description: B-field Z-component in Planetocentric coordinate system.
columns.name: BZ PLANETOCENTRIC

columns.description:
Instrument dynamic range identifier at time of the sample.
Pertains to B components.
columns.name: INSTRUMENT RANGE

columns.description: Spacecraft position X-component in Planetocentric coordinate system.
columns.name: X

columns.description: Spacecraft position Y-component in Planetocentric coordinate system.
columns.name: Y

columns.description: Spacecraft position Z-component in Planetocentric coordinate system.
columns.name: Z

table_description:
The magnetic field data are stored in a fixed field ASCII table
structure that immediately follows the attached header.  This table
contains time-tagged rows of magnetic field values and instrument
dynamic range identifiers.
productdescription:
This file contains vector magnetic field data acquired by the
Fluxgate Magnetometer instrument aboard the Juno spacecraft.
The data are calibrated and provided in physical units (nT).
The data has been downsampled to 1 second to provide a more
compact dataset.  The data are expressed in
Planetocentric coordinates.
